  "text": "The clinical and laboratory data included the duration from symptom onset to admission, appetite change prior to admission, the daily average dietary intake from the day after admission to the follow-up analysis, albumin concentration, the presence of septic shock, inpatient death, and primary sources of infection (refer to Supplemental Online Materials for definitions). The dietary intake of the first week after admission was divided into 3 categories (low, ,15 kcal/kg/d; moderate, 15 to 30 kcal/kg/d; adequate, $30 kcal/kg/d), as determined by the required amount of energy in geriatric patients [CITATION_1] .",
